  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a developer, I want to use the fastest safe crypto possible, so I have a good user experience.\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature/Perf\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Replace ECCJS (SJCL) library with libsodium/chloride while keeping interface and check perf.\r\n\r\n- [ ] Try libsodium/chloride while keeping interface same\r\n- [ ] Make a solid benchmark comparing current encrypt/decrypt function vs libsodium/chloride\r\n\r\nSee https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/23399c63e172479876fe2a76b4eb9f5b9785f9b5/src/status_im/protocol/encryption.cljs\r\n\r\nAdditional context:\r\n- Following our eccjs lib and issues I see perf is basically untouched. Someone who has done a lot of work on this a guy called Dominic Tarr (see https://github.com/jpillora/eccjs/issues/3 and https://dominictarr.github.io/crypto-bench/ and https://github.com/dominictarr/chloride ).\r\n- https://twitter.com/oskarth/status/944289740739801088 (EDIT: Oops, I cleaned all my tweets, his reply: https://twitter.com/dominictarr/status/944428656591388672)\r\n  ",
